{
  "text": "A cohort of 32 shells were implanted into eight cadavers, the details of which have been published previously, [CITATION_1] and are summarised in Table 1 . Multiple shells were implanted into each acetabulum where the surgeon deemed it suitable. In these instances, the surgeon would remove the previous acetabular shell and rereamed by at least 1 mm to accommodate the next shell size up.",
